justification: Fever and seizures are common presenting symptoms of encephalitis. Atrophic scarring can occur with brain inflammation and damage. Arthropathy, while less common, can be a rare complication.}, {diagnosis: Cerebral malaria

justification: Fever and seizures are hallmark symptoms. Cerebral malaria can lead to neurological complications, including brain damage that might manifest as atrophic scarring. Arthropathy can be a rare complication.}, {diagnosis: Neurocysticercosis

justification: Caused by a parasitic infection in the brain. Seizures are a common symptom, and depending on the location and severity of the infection, it can lead to fever. Brain lesions from the parasite can cause atrophy and scarring. Arthropathy is less common but can occur as a systemic reaction.}, {diagnosis: Autoimmune encephalitis

justification: Characterized by brain inflammation. Fever, seizures, and cognitive changes are common. Long-term inflammation can cause brain atrophy and scarring. Some forms of autoimmune encephalitis can also cause joint involvement (arthropathy).}, {diagnosis: Tuberculous meningitis

justification: Serious infection of the brain and spinal cord.  Fever, headache, stiff neck, seizures are common. Neurological complications can lead to brain damage and potential scarring.  Joint involvement can occur.}, {diagnosis: Lyme neuroborreliosis

justification: Late-stage Lyme disease can affect the nervous system.  Fever, neurological symptoms (including seizures), and joint pain (arthropathy) are possible. While less common, chronic inflammation could potentially lead to scarring.}, {diagnosis: Neurosarcoidosis

justification: Growth of inflammatory cells in the nervous system.  Can present with fever, seizures, and neurological deficits. Chronic inflammation might potentially lead to scarring. Sarcoidosis can involve joints.}, {diagnosis: HIV-related encephalopathy

justification: Infection and inflammation of the brain due to HIV.  Fever, seizures, and cognitive decline can occur.  In advanced stages, brain atrophy might be observed. Joint pain is common in HIV.}, {diagnosis: Behçets disease

justification: Rare autoimmune disease affecting blood vessels.  Presents with mouth sores, genital sores, and eye inflammation.  Can affect the nervous system (neuro-Behçets) causing neurological symptoms like seizures.  Arthropathy is a common feature.  Scarring can occur with repeated inflammation.}, {diagnosis: Substance-induced seizures and complications

justification: Certain substances can trigger seizures and potentially lead to brain damage with repeated episodes, possibly causing scarring.  Fever can occur during withdrawal.  Some substances can also cause joint pain.}
